    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Unfortunately, we don't have per-platform magic that informs gRPC on how to use the platforms roots.\nIf you install gRPC, it will use by default the roots shipped with gRPC (they come from Mozilla and are updated about every month): see https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/etc/roots.pem\n\nIf you want to use the debian ones, I suggest that you set the `GRPC_DEFAULT_SSL_ROOTS_FILE_PATH` env variable to `/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt`. Does that make sense?\n"
  },
